[This is clearly a busy season for vesicular stomatitis. Kansas appears to be a hot spot, or their media is much better at getting the word out. However, it remains disappointing that the USDA has stopped reporting the strains. The strain may not change the outcome of the situation, but for those of us tracking the disease, it is frustrating to know there were 2 strains at the beginning of this very busy VSV season, and now it is all lumped into one category, without allowing tracking of the different and locations of the different strains. - Mod.TG

